Full job description

Company Overview:
Aebocode Technologies is a leading Australian-based company specializing in innovative technology solutions across various industries. We provide top-quality drone services, including survey services. Additionally, we offer a range of products such as smart panels for communication and collaboration in office and educational environments, and robotics kits for kids, fostering hands-on learning and creativity.

Job Role:
You will lead the design of the Ground Control Station, oversee the anti-drone system project. Your role involves testing, collaboration with cross-functional teams, and addressing technical issues to advance drone technology and ensure project success.

Key Responsibilities:

  • Develop software for Ground Control Stations, anti-drone systems, and smart classroom solutions.
  • Conduct thorough testing and validation procedures.
  • Deploy software tools, processes, and metrics.
  • Collaborate with departments on project status and proposals.
  • Analyze system requirements and recommend modifications or new system installations.
  • Evaluate software-hardware interfaces and develop specifications and performance requirements.
  • Design and develop software systems using scientific analysis and mathematical models.
  • Prepare reports on project specifications, activities, and status.

Requirements:

  • Master's or Bachelor's degree in computer science or a related field.
  • Minimum 3 years of experience in software development.
  • Proficiency in Qt, QML, C++, C#, and MAVLink protocol.
  • Ability to thrive in a fast-paced environment.
  • Strong team player with a positive attitude.
  • Experience working on various software development projects.

Note: Experience in the QGroundControl (QGC) field, including Qt, QML, C++, C#, and MAVLink protocol, is highly desirable.

Additional Skills (Preferred): Familiarity with JavaScript frameworks such as HTML, CSS, PHP, Python, NodeJS, React, and Vue.

Job Type: Full-time

Salary: ₹500,000.00 per year
